beer.beer_description:
Very dark, sweet full-bodied ale. The milk name is derived from the use of lactose (milk sugar) which imparts a residual sweetness and nice creamy mouthfeel. Dark roasted malt impression with rich chocolate and coffee characters. Perfect for a winter's day!
Malts: Pilsner malt(GER), chocolate malt (ENG), wheat malt, roast barley.
Hops: AUS Cascade
Sugars: Lactose

Hop Bitterness- Low (12IBU)
Hop Aroma- Low (0.5g/L)
Colour- Very Dark (57 EBC)
Drinkability- When it's raining, all day (moderate)
